and spirituality, as well.

00:03:12.950 --> 00:03:15.590 align:middle line:90%
So we co-organized a meeting.

00:03:15.590 --> 00:03:19.530 align:middle line:10%
And in this meeting, many
famous scientists attended,

00:03:19.530 --> 00:03:24.490 align:middle line:10%
and they were all scientists
who do not believe anymore

00:03:24.490 --> 00:03:28.730 align:middle line:10%
in the old materialist
worldview in science.

00:03:28.730 --> 00:03:31.480 align:middle line:10%
And people like
Rupert Sheldrake,

00:03:31.480 --> 00:03:36.400 align:middle line:10%
for instance, or Larry
Dossey, Pim van Lommel,

00:03:36.400 --> 00:03:39.810 align:middle line:10%
and so on and so forth, and
a great group of people.

00:03:39.810 --> 00:03:43.970 align:middle line:10%
And we have decided to create
a new scientific organization

00:03:43.970 --> 00:03:46.370 align:middle line:10%
which we call post materialist.

00:03:46.370 --> 00:03:51.520 align:middle line:84%
So now, because materialism
has been the dominant view--

00:03:51.520 --> 00:03:56.780 align:middle line:84%
or the dominant paradigm
in science for nearly four

00:03:56.780 --> 00:03:58.380 align:middle line:90%
centuries now.

00:03:58.380 --> 00:04:02.220 align:middle line:84%
But it started to be challenged
100 years ago by quantum

00:04:02.220 --> 00:04:03.560 align:middle line:90%
physics.

00:04:03.560 --> 00:04:06.110 align:middle line:84%
But in the other
scientific disciplines,

00:04:06.110 --> 00:04:11.230 align:middle line:84%
like medicine, for instance, or
biomedical research, biology,

00:04:11.230 --> 00:04:14.400 align:middle line:84%
neuroscience, the
materialist view

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:17.250 align:middle line:90%
is still quite influential.

00:04:17.250 --> 00:04:20.029 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: But this wasn't
always the case, right?

00:04:20.029 --> 00:04:22.870 align:middle line:84%
So if we look back in
history and the origins

00:04:22.870 --> 00:04:26.300 align:middle line:84%
before really things
became material,

00:04:26.300 --> 00:04:28.180 align:middle line:90%
it was not before that, was it?

00:04:28.180 --> 00:04:29.320 align:middle line:90%
Or how did it progress?

00:04:29.320 --> 00:04:32.657 align:middle line:84%
Because a little by little, it
went more and more materialist.

00:04:32.657 --> 00:04:34.240 align:middle line:84%
That's what you're
saying in the book.

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:38.040 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Actually, at
the beginning of science,

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:40.630 align:middle line:84%
the fathers of what we
call modern science, 400

00:04:40.630 --> 00:04:45.160 align:middle line:84%
years ago-- all of these people
were deeply spiritual and also

00:04:45.160 --> 00:04:45.810 align:middle line:90%
religious.

00:04:45.810 --> 00:04:49.590 align:middle line:84%
People like Isaac Newton
or Rene Descartes,

00:04:49.590 --> 00:04:53.210 align:middle line:84%
for instance, or
even Galileo Galilei.

00:04:53.210 --> 00:04:58.830 align:middle line:84%
But after a few hundred
years following them,

00:04:58.830 --> 00:05:01.490 align:middle line:90%
there was a big change.

00:05:01.490 --> 00:05:06.320 align:middle line:84%
Scientists became to
believe only in the matter.

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:09.500 align:middle line:84%
Because the fathers
of modern science,

00:05:09.500 --> 00:05:12.110 align:middle line:84%
Descartes and so
on and so forth,

00:05:12.110 --> 00:05:15.370 align:middle line:84%
proposed a number
of basic postulates

00:05:15.370 --> 00:05:18.680 align:middle line:84%
about the nature
of reality and how

00:05:18.680 --> 00:05:21.240 align:middle line:90%
we can investigate these things.

00:05:21.240 --> 00:05:23.300 align:middle line:84%
One of the principals
they proposed

00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:27.245 align:middle line:84%
was that everything in the
universe is composed of matter.

00:05:27.245 --> 00:05:29.860 align:middle line:90%


00:05:29.860 --> 00:05:33.060 align:middle line:84%
But these pioneers
knew that there

00:05:33.060 --> 00:05:35.350 align:middle line:90%
was something else than matter.

00:05:35.350 --> 00:05:37.140 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact,
they all believed

00:05:37.140 --> 00:05:39.840 align:middle line:84%
that what we call
matter was created

00:05:39.840 --> 00:05:44.160 align:middle line:84%
by a sort of
intelligent designer

00:05:44.160 --> 00:05:46.500 align:middle line:84%
at the origin of
everything in the universe.

00:05:46.500 --> 00:05:51.125 align:middle line:84%
But this was forgotten after
a few centuries of science.

00:05:51.125 --> 00:05:54.290 align:middle line:90%


00:05:54.290 --> 00:05:57.810 align:middle line:84%
During the 19th century, for
instance, scientists only

00:05:57.810 --> 00:06:01.890 align:middle line:84%
kept these basic assumptions
about the universe.

00:06:01.890 --> 00:06:05.220 align:middle line:84%
But they started to think
that perhaps it was not

00:06:05.220 --> 00:06:10.000 align:middle line:84%
necessary to refer to
an intelligent source

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:13.130 align:middle line:84%
at the origin of
everything in the universe.

00:06:13.130 --> 00:06:18.040 align:middle line:84%
So they started to believe that
matter itself could explain

00:06:18.040 --> 00:06:22.160 align:middle line:84%
everything, including
us, human beings.

00:06:22.160 --> 00:06:25.230 align:middle line:84%
But during the 20th
century, and also

00:06:25.230 --> 00:06:27.880 align:middle line:84%
the beginning of
the 21st century,

00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:32.480 align:middle line:84%
we have collected so many data
in various fields of science

00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:36.320 align:middle line:84%
that we know for sure now
that this old materialist

00:06:36.320 --> 00:06:42.000 align:middle line:84%
worldview is totally
wrong, completely wrong.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:43.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Spinning
together right now

00:06:43.790 --> 00:06:46.710 align:middle line:84%
and bridging that is
very, very important.

00:06:46.710 --> 00:06:48.500 align:middle line:90%
What various fields such as--

00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:51.260 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well,
you have physics.

00:06:51.260 --> 00:06:56.060 align:middle line:84%
You have biology, biomedical
research, neuroscience,

00:06:56.060 --> 00:06:59.640 align:middle line:84%
psychiatry, and
psychology, as well.

00:06:59.640 --> 00:07:04.800 align:middle line:84%
So now you have scientists in
these various fields believing

00:07:04.800 --> 00:07:07.840 align:middle line:84%
that it's time to get
rid of the old paradigm

00:07:07.840 --> 00:07:10.470 align:middle line:84%
and to switch to
something totally new,

00:07:10.470 --> 00:07:13.252 align:middle line:90%
that we called post materialist.

00:07:13.252 --> 00:07:15.419 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: I'm very interested
to get into, of course,

00:07:15.419 --> 00:07:17.543 align:middle line:84%
the conversation of--
because your book, in French,

