worldview is flat wrong.

00:07:54.350 --> 00:07:56.800 align:middle line:90%
So there's a big conflict there.

00:07:56.800 --> 00:07:58.750 align:middle line:90%
Hence, the title Brain Wars.

00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:03.530 align:middle line:84%
In French, it was
called the [FRENCH]

00:08:03.530 --> 00:08:05.940 align:middle line:84%
because-- so the powers
of consciousness and mind

00:08:05.940 --> 00:08:09.830 align:middle line:84%
because this is one
line of evidence showing

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:14.770 align:middle line:84%
that the materialist
view is erroneous.

00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:18.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: I love when you get
into the whole-- well, first

00:08:18.420 --> 00:08:19.340 align:middle line:90%
the placebo.

00:08:19.340 --> 00:08:21.100 align:middle line:84%
We can talk about
it and start there.

00:08:21.100 --> 00:08:22.930 align:middle line:90%
The placebo-nocebo effect.

00:08:22.930 --> 00:08:26.970 align:middle line:84%
And how even, I didn't
realize, but it also

00:08:26.970 --> 00:08:31.466 align:middle line:84%
has an effect even on physical
surgeries and problems.

00:08:31.466 --> 00:08:34.049 align:middle line:84%
Tell us more about that because
we don't talk enough about it,

00:08:34.049 --> 00:08:34.549 align:middle line:90%
I think.

00:08:34.549 --> 00:08:35.990 align:middle line:90%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yes.

00:08:35.990 --> 00:08:40.360 align:middle line:84%
The placebo effect is based on
the belief and the expectations

00:08:40.360 --> 00:08:43.390 align:middle line:84%
about a treatment
that is fake, sham.

00:08:43.390 --> 00:08:47.070 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have any real effect
biologically or medically.

00:08:47.070 --> 00:08:50.990 align:middle line:84%
Still, it as an effect
on the body just because

00:08:50.990 --> 00:08:53.230 align:middle line:90%
of your belief about it.

00:08:53.230 --> 00:08:58.810 align:middle line:84%
And it plays a role in all sorts
of medical and psychological

00:08:58.810 --> 00:09:01.510 align:middle line:84%
interventions,
including surgery.

00:09:01.510 --> 00:09:03.525 align:middle line:90%
So for instance--

00:09:03.525 --> 00:09:04.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: So a
person that thought

00:09:04.900 --> 00:09:06.950 align:middle line:84%
they had a surgery, for
example, at the knees,

00:09:06.950 --> 00:09:08.360 align:middle line:84%
but they didn't
have the surgery.

00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:10.540 align:middle line:84%
They just-- somebody put
something on top of it.

00:09:10.540 --> 00:09:11.990 align:middle line:90%
I mean a plaster.

00:09:11.990 --> 00:09:14.610 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: And scrape
the skin, for instance,

00:09:14.610 --> 00:09:16.120 align:middle line:90%
and made a small incision.

00:09:16.120 --> 00:09:17.780 align:middle line:84%
That was study
that has been done

00:09:17.780 --> 00:09:20.760 align:middle line:84%
in the '90s at Baylor
College in Houston

00:09:20.760 --> 00:09:23.560 align:middle line:90%
by Bruce Moseley, a surgeon.

00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:26.340 align:middle line:84%
And most of these people
were not even able

00:09:26.340 --> 00:09:30.360 align:middle line:84%
to-- they were walking with
canes before the intervention.

00:09:30.360 --> 00:09:34.630 align:middle line:84%
And after the
intervention, most of them

00:09:34.630 --> 00:09:38.680 align:middle line:84%
were even able to play
sports, including basketball,

00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:41.720 align:middle line:84%
even though they
received the placebo

00:09:41.720 --> 00:09:43.860 align:middle line:90%
surgery, the fake surgery.

00:09:43.860 --> 00:09:47.310 align:middle line:84%
So it shows that our minds
can be extremely powerful.

00:09:47.310 --> 00:09:49.700 align:middle line:84%
And there was another
very interesting study

00:09:49.700 --> 00:09:51.510 align:middle line:90%
about a placebo.

00:09:51.510 --> 00:09:53.480 align:middle line:84%
It was done with
people suffering

00:09:53.480 --> 00:09:55.470 align:middle line:90%
from Parkinson's disease.

00:09:55.470 --> 00:09:58.800 align:middle line:84%
And in Parkinson's disease,
you have destruction

00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:03.060 align:middle line:84%
of the neurons in the brain
producing a chemical messenger

00:10:03.060 --> 00:10:05.120 align:middle line:90%
that we call dopamine.

00:10:05.120 --> 00:10:08.380 align:middle line:84%
And in the case
of those patients,

00:10:08.380 --> 00:10:12.240 align:middle line:84%
the level of destruction
was about 75-80%

00:10:12.240 --> 00:10:14.670 align:middle line:90%
so it was quite severe.

00:10:14.670 --> 00:10:18.500 align:middle line:84%
And so these people
were very handicapped

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:19.840 align:middle line:90%
from a motor point of view.

00:10:19.840 --> 00:10:23.010 align:middle line:90%
They had trouble moving.

00:10:23.010 --> 00:10:25.243 align:middle line:84%
They were experiencing a
lot of tremors and rigidity

00:10:25.243 --> 00:10:27.850 align:middle line:90%
and so on and so forth.

00:10:27.850 --> 00:10:32.690 align:middle line:84%
The doctors told these patients
that they had found something

00:10:32.690 --> 00:10:36.990 align:middle line:84%
new, a miracle cure for,
possibly, for Parkinson's.

00:10:36.990 --> 00:10:41.060 align:middle line:84%
And so those patients
who most believe in it,

00:10:41.060 --> 00:10:43.290 align:middle line:84%
they started to
produce, in their brain,

00:10:43.290 --> 00:10:46.310 align:middle line:84%
dopamine in amounts
comparable to what

00:10:46.310 --> 00:10:49.240 align:middle line:84%
you see in very young
people, people 20 years old,

00:10:49.240 --> 00:10:50.430 align:middle line:90%
for instance.

00:10:50.430 --> 00:10:55.240 align:middle line:84%
And so there was also
clinical improvement

00:10:55.240 --> 00:10:58.547 align:middle line:84%
in terms of their ability to
move, less tremor and rigidity

00:10:58.547 --> 00:11:01.240 align:middle line:84%
and so on and so
forth for a while,

00:11:01.240 --> 00:11:03.320 align:middle line:90%
because it doesn't last forever.

00:11:03.320 --> 00:11:05.702 align:middle line:90%
Still, this is quite impressive.

00:11:05.702 --> 00:11:08.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: So the body is able
to produce all those chemicals

00:11:08.160 --> 00:11:09.221 align:middle line:90%
by itself?

00:11:09.221 --> 00:11:09.970 align:middle line:90%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yes.

00:11:09.970 --> 00:11:12.114 align:middle line:90%
But you have to influence it.

00:11:12.114 --> 00:11:21.320 align:middle line:84%
You-- We play a-- You have to
give your body the exact orders

00:11:21.320 --> 00:11:23.730 align:middle line:90%
to create such an effect.

00:11:23.730 --> 00:11:27.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Yet it seems quite
spontaneous and those patients

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:29.710 align:middle line:84%
didn't know anything about
traditional science, I guess,

00:11:29.710 --> 00:11:30.350 align:middle line:90%
or the dosage.

00:11:30.350 --> 00:11:31.058 align:middle line:90%
>>BEAUREGARD: No.

00:11:31.058 --> 00:11:32.610 align:middle line:84%
Because in the case
of the placebo,

00:11:32.610 --> 00:11:34.570 align:middle line:90%
it's an unconscious process.

00:11:34.570 --> 00:11:36.920 align:middle line:90%
It's not conscious.

00:11:36.920 --> 00:11:41.940 align:middle line:84%
So you just have to believe
and expect good things

00:11:41.940 --> 00:11:44.860 align:middle line:84%
about the treatment,
and it will happen.

00:11:44.860 --> 00:11:49.120 align:middle line:84%
And now we know that it's part
of every sort of treatments.

00:11:49.120 --> 00:11:54.520 align:middle line:84%
Whenever you see a medical
doctor, a shaman, healer--

00:11:54.520 --> 00:11:57.850 align:middle line:84%
it's active in all
sorts of traditions

00:11:57.850 --> 00:12:02.000 align:middle line:84%
and for all kinds of treatments,
psychological and physical

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:03.250 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:12:03.250 --> 00:12:05.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: So I guess
the relationship

00:12:05.660 --> 00:12:08.160 align:middle line:84%
between the doctor or the
healer and the patient

00:12:08.160 --> 00:12:09.150 align:middle line:90%
is very important.

00:12:09.150 --> 00:12:13.874 align:middle line:84%
There should be a resonance or
some kind of alignment there.

00:12:13.874 --> 00:12:15.290 align:middle line:84%
Because otherwise
it doesn't work.

00:12:15.290 --> 00:12:16.040 align:middle line:90%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yes.

00:12:16.040 --> 00:12:19.460 align:middle line:84%
So now there are studies
showing that to generate

00:12:19.460 --> 00:12:23.820 align:middle line:84%
a much stronger placebo
effect, the relationship

00:12:23.820 --> 00:12:27.470 align:middle line:90%
with the therapist is crucial.

00:12:27.470 --> 00:12:28.720 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:12:28.720 --> 00:12:32.870 align:middle line:84%
Because if you don't have a
good rapport with the therapist,

00:12:32.870 --> 00:12:37.310 align:middle line:84%
then the placebo effect
will be much smaller.

00:12:37.310 --> 00:12:42.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: So how does this
consciousness actually

00:12:42.270 --> 00:12:43.590 align:middle line:90%
interact with us?

00:12:43.590 --> 00:12:46.390 align:middle line:84%
Or how can we
align with it so we

00:12:46.390 --> 00:12:52.400 align:middle line:84%
can have the benefits
and the effect of being

00:12:52.400 --> 00:12:58.660 align:middle line:84%
part of something larger,
bigger, and really even

00:12:58.660 --> 00:13:01.630 align:middle line:84%
[FRENCH], self-healing,
and things like that?

00:13:01.630 --> 00:13:03.090 align:middle line:90%
How is that possible?

00:13:03.090 --> 00:13:04.530 align:middle line:90%
Is that a state of mind?

00:13:04.530 --> 00:13:06.250 align:middle line:90%
Is that a way of seeing things?

00:13:06.250 --> 00:13:08.120 align:middle line:90%
You talked about belief earlier.

00:13:08.120 --> 00:13:09.570 align:middle line:90%
Is it part of the brain?

00:13:09.570 --> 00:13:12.310 align:middle line:84%
Is there a particular
portion of the brain

00:13:12.310 --> 00:13:13.700 align:middle line:90%
that will activate that?

00:13:13.700 --> 00:13:15.700 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well,
it's several things.

00:13:15.700 --> 00:13:20.080 align:middle line:84%
It's beliefs,
positive expectations,

00:13:20.080 --> 00:13:23.380 align:middle line:84%
a positive relationship
with the therapist.

00:13:23.380 --> 00:13:25.090 align:middle line:84%
It's also a matter
of perception:

00:13:25.090 --> 00:13:29.990 align:middle line:84%
how you see yourself and your
beliefs about your disease

00:13:29.990 --> 00:13:34.490 align:middle line:84%
and your body and your
capacity, as well.

00:13:34.490 --> 00:13:39.040 align:middle line:84%
So it's a mix of
several factors.

00:13:39.040 --> 00:13:43.240 align:middle line:84%
But you can influence
that to a certain extent.

00:13:43.240 --> 00:13:48.550 align:middle line:84%
So if you're confident
about the outcome,

00:13:48.550 --> 00:13:51.030 align:middle line:84%
if you have a good relationship,
like we were saying,

00:13:51.030 --> 00:13:55.840 align:middle line:84%
with the therapist, then
likelihood to get very strong,

00:13:55.840 --> 00:13:58.450 align:middle line:90%
positive results is much higher.

00:13:58.450 --> 00:14:02.354 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Tell us about
the neurofeedback or--

00:14:02.354 --> 00:14:04.020 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD:
Neurofeedback-- well, it's

00:14:04.020 --> 00:14:08.560 align:middle line:84%
a technique where you learn
to control your own brain's

00:14:08.560 --> 00:14:10.530 align:middle line:90%
electrical activity.

00:14:10.530 --> 00:14:13.470 align:middle line:90%
And you do that on purpose.

00:14:13.470 --> 00:14:17.560 align:middle line:84%
So you have to have the
intention of doing this.

00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:20.810 align:middle line:84%
And so you have electrodes
recording your brain

00:14:20.810 --> 00:14:22.670 align:middle line:90%
electrical activity.

00:14:22.670 --> 00:14:25.650 align:middle line:84%
And the electrical
activity, recorded

00:14:25.650 --> 00:14:28.450 align:middle line:84%
at the level of the
electrodes, it's

00:14:28.450 --> 00:14:31.050 align:middle line:90%
translated through a video game.

00:14:31.050 --> 00:14:34.330 align:middle line:84%
It's converted under the
form of a video game.

00:14:34.330 --> 00:14:38.330 align:middle line:84%
And so when you're in the
right zone-- for instance,

00:14:38.330 --> 00:14:42.720 align:middle line:84%
if you take the case of a
child suffering from attention

00:14:42.720 --> 00:14:44.720 align:middle line:90%
deficit disorder, for instance.

00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:47.500 align:middle line:84%
They can have too
much slow waves

00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:50.320 align:middle line:84%
in the most anterior
portion of the brain,

00:14:50.320 --> 00:14:53.160 align:middle line:90%
what we call the frontal cortex.

00:14:53.160 --> 00:14:59.160 align:middle line:84%
So the training
seeks to increase,

00:14:59.160 --> 00:15:02.930 align:middle line:84%
to speed up, the brain
waves in such a case.

00:15:02.930 --> 00:15:07.190 align:middle line:84%
And so, if the child,
when he's able to do that,

00:15:07.190 --> 00:15:13.540 align:middle line:84%
the video game-- it can be
racing cars or anything else--

00:15:13.540 --> 00:15:15.200 align:middle line:90%
it moves forward.

00:15:15.200 --> 00:15:16.570 align:middle line:90%
There's animation.

00:15:16.570 --> 00:15:21.230 align:middle line:84%
And each time the child
gets out of the zone,

00:15:21.230 --> 00:15:23.690 align:middle line:84%
the target zone,
everything stops.

00:15:23.690 --> 00:15:28.260 align:middle line:84%
So and there's no music anymore
and no cartoons and everything

00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:29.090 align:middle line:90%
freezes.

00:15:29.090 --> 00:15:31.690 align:middle line:84%
So that's how the
child can learn.

00:15:31.690 --> 00:15:36.270 align:middle line:84%
He's receiving a feedback
about his own brain

00:15:36.270 --> 00:15:37.780 align:middle line:90%
electrical activity.

00:15:37.780 --> 00:15:43.690 align:middle line:84%
And for most people, you can
start controlling your brain

00:15:43.690 --> 00:15:49.880 align:middle line:84%
activity after 15-20 minutes,
usually, to a certain extent.

00:15:49.880 --> 00:15:53.240 align:middle line:84%
And if you repeat, in terms
of the number of sessions

00:15:53.240 --> 00:15:57.490 align:middle line:84%
of training, after, for
instance, 30 sessions,

00:15:57.490 --> 00:16:00.030 align:middle line:84%
you are much better
at doing this.

00:16:00.030 --> 00:16:04.150 align:middle line:84%
In the case of children
with attention deficit

00:16:04.150 --> 00:16:07.910 align:middle line:84%
and hyperactivity, they don't
need medications anymore

00:16:07.910 --> 00:16:12.620 align:middle line:84%
after, sometimes, 35-40 sessions
of neurofeedback training.

00:16:12.620 --> 00:16:14.250 align:middle line:90%
So this is very impressive.

00:16:14.250 --> 00:16:18.940 align:middle line:84%
And we've done studies in my lab
showing that when you do that,

00:16:18.940 --> 00:16:22.770 align:middle line:84%
you change the functioning
of the brain regions involved

00:16:22.770 --> 00:16:25.570 align:middle line:84%
in, for instance,
attention, concentration,

00:16:25.570 --> 00:16:27.620 align:middle line:90%
and so on and so forth.

00:16:27.620 --> 00:16:31.450 align:middle line:84%
But now we know also
that you can even

00:16:31.450 --> 00:16:33.530 align:middle line:84%
alter the structure
of the brain.

00:16:33.530 --> 00:16:37.994 align:middle line:84%
So you can increase the density
of white matter, gray matter.

00:16:37.994 --> 00:16:39.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Tell us about that.

00:16:39.160 --> 00:16:42.300 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to ask you more about
the white matter in the brain.

00:16:42.300 --> 00:16:44.220 align:middle line:90%
What role does it play?

00:16:44.220 --> 00:16:46.034 align:middle line:84%
And could it actually
really increase?

00:16:46.034 --> 00:16:47.450 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: So
the white matter,

00:16:47.450 --> 00:16:53.190 align:middle line:84%
it's nerve fibers connecting
neurons in various regions,

00:16:53.190 --> 00:16:57.180 align:middle line:84%
different regions, two
regions, for instance, A and B.

00:16:57.180 --> 00:17:00.450 align:middle line:84%
So if you increase the
density of white matter,

00:17:00.450 --> 00:17:04.069 align:middle line:84%
in principle, you will--
you can increase also

00:17:04.069 --> 00:17:08.760 align:middle line:84%
the speed of transmission of
the information between the two

00:17:08.760 --> 00:17:10.030 align:middle line:90%
regions.

00:17:10.030 --> 00:17:13.450 align:middle line:84%
So the brain becomes more
efficient, if you will,

00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:17.980 align:middle line:84%
in terms of
information processing.

00:17:17.980 --> 00:17:21.500 align:middle line:84%
And you can also increase
the gray matter composed

00:17:21.500 --> 00:17:24.550 align:middle line:84%
of the nerve cells
themselves, the neurons,

00:17:24.550 --> 00:17:26.470 align:middle line:90%
the density of neurons.

00:17:26.470 --> 00:17:31.170 align:middle line:84%
So now we know that the
brain is extremely plastic.

00:17:31.170 --> 00:17:33.780 align:middle line:84%
We use the term
neural plasticity.

00:17:33.780 --> 00:17:39.340 align:middle line:84%
And even the adult
brain is quite plastic.

00:17:39.340 --> 00:17:43.837 align:middle line:84%
And it lasts all life
long, across the lifespan.

00:17:43.837 --> 00:17:45.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Even neurons, actually?

00:17:45.170 --> 00:17:47.520 align:middle line:84%
Because we heard a lot
that we kill them if

00:17:47.520 --> 00:17:50.250 align:middle line:90%
we drink or do this or do that.

00:17:50.250 --> 00:17:51.830 align:middle line:90%
And across our lifetime?

00:17:51.830 --> 00:17:53.400 align:middle line:90%
How does that work for you?

00:17:53.400 --> 00:17:57.920 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well, that's right
that we kill them, depending

00:17:57.920 --> 00:18:01.510 align:middle line:84%
on what you ingest, what
you eat, what you drink.

00:18:01.510 --> 00:18:04.290 align:middle line:84%
Alcohol, for instance,
is very toxic.

00:18:04.290 --> 00:18:08.870 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, if
you try to learn things,

00:18:08.870 --> 00:18:12.730 align:middle line:84%
if you read books, if
you watch even movies,

00:18:12.730 --> 00:18:16.490 align:middle line:84%
or you can even play video
games-- you will create

00:18:16.490 --> 00:18:18.810 align:middle line:84%
new neurons in your
brain and especially

00:18:18.810 --> 00:18:22.390 align:middle line:84%
in certain portions of the brain
related to learning and memory,

00:18:22.390 --> 00:18:25.390 align:middle line:90%
like the hippocampus.

00:18:25.390 --> 00:18:26.510 align:middle line:90%
So we know that.

00:18:26.510 --> 00:18:31.250 align:middle line:84%
And since there's a lot of
plasticity in our brains,

00:18:31.250 --> 00:18:35.882 align:middle line:84%
it's possible to slow
down aging in that way.

00:18:35.882 --> 00:18:37.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Some people
go all the way

00:18:37.340 --> 00:18:40.090 align:middle line:90%
to talking about immortality.

00:18:40.090 --> 00:18:42.030 align:middle line:90%
Where are you at in that matter?

00:18:42.030 --> 00:18:43.970 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well,
scientifically, it's

00:18:43.970 --> 00:18:50.919 align:middle line:84%
not been demonstrated yet, but
we know it may be possible.

00:18:50.919 --> 00:18:52.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: You get into hypnosis.

00:18:52.210 --> 00:18:53.380 align:middle line:90%
And I was quite excited.

00:18:53.380 --> 00:18:55.713 align:middle line:84%
And I know I'm going to do
another interview with Rachal

00:18:55.713 --> 00:18:59.580 align:middle line:84%
here-- and what's his last
name, Chaboux-- on hypnosis.

00:18:59.580 --> 00:19:02.070 align:middle line:84%
But I was quite surprised
to see it in the book.

00:19:02.070 --> 00:19:03.000 align:middle line:90%
How do you see it?

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:04.450 align:middle line:90%
What's your angle on it?

00:19:04.450 --> 00:19:06.410 align:middle line:84%
Because I think it's
quite misunderstood.

00:19:06.410 --> 00:19:07.160 align:middle line:90%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yes.

00:19:07.160 --> 00:19:10.700 align:middle line:84%
So people think that
when you do hypnosis

00:19:10.700 --> 00:19:15.350 align:middle line:84%
and you're the subject,
you give your control

00:19:15.350 --> 00:19:16.780 align:middle line:90%
away to the hypnotist.

00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:19.940 align:middle line:84%
But the people,
the psychologists

00:19:19.940 --> 00:19:22.160 align:middle line:84%
doing study, scientific
studies, about hypnosis,

00:19:22.160 --> 00:19:27.820 align:middle line:84%
now they know that hypnosis
is always self-hypnosis.

00:19:27.820 --> 00:19:31.440 align:middle line:84%
So it means that if you don't
want to become hypnotized,

00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:34.210 align:middle line:84%
if you don't listen to
the suggestions made

00:19:34.210 --> 00:19:36.755 align:middle line:84%
by the hypnotherapist,
it won't work.

00:19:36.755 --> 00:19:44.310 align:middle line:84%
Nobody will be able to-- So you
have-- You're bringing yourself

00:19:44.310 --> 00:19:46.300 align:middle line:84%
into an altered state
of consciousness

00:19:46.300 --> 00:19:50.296 align:middle line:84%
when you do that, if
you play the game.

00:19:50.296 --> 00:19:51.587 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: What does it work for?

00:19:51.587 --> 00:19:53.300 align:middle line:90%
What is it good for?

00:19:53.300 --> 00:19:55.600 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: All sorts of--
well, clinical purposes,

00:19:55.600 --> 00:20:01.260 align:middle line:84%
for instance, so phobia,
it can be very good.

00:20:01.260 --> 00:20:06.300 align:middle line:84%
Even depressive symptoms
and so on and so forth.

00:20:06.300 --> 00:20:10.370 align:middle line:84%
It can also have a physical
impact on the body.

00:20:10.370 --> 00:20:14.880 align:middle line:84%
There was a study done about the
speed of healing of fractures.

00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:18.400 align:middle line:84%
And it was done at
Harvard years ago.

00:20:18.400 --> 00:20:24.470 align:middle line:84%
And they have found that
if the patients were doing

00:20:24.470 --> 00:20:27.610 align:middle line:84%
self-hypnosis a few
times every week

00:20:27.610 --> 00:20:31.470 align:middle line:84%
for four weeks,
for instance, they

00:20:31.470 --> 00:20:37.470 align:middle line:84%
were increasing the speed
of healing considerably

00:20:37.470 --> 00:20:40.790 align:middle line:90%
by a very important percentage.

00:20:40.790 --> 00:20:47.580 align:middle line:84%
So you can influence, it seems,
every process in the body

00:20:47.580 --> 00:20:50.960 align:middle line:84%
and in the brain
using this technique.

00:20:50.960 --> 00:20:53.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: When we slow down,
is it because we slow down

00:20:53.210 --> 00:20:57.130 align:middle line:84%
and we reach other
levels, deeper levels.

00:20:57.130 --> 00:20:59.280 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well,
about that, there's not

00:20:59.280 --> 00:21:02.830 align:middle line:84%
been a lot of studies regarding
the brain waves associated

00:21:02.830 --> 00:21:03.590 align:middle line:90%
with hypnosis.

00:21:03.590 --> 00:21:06.270 align:middle line:84%
But what we know, so
far, is that there's

00:21:06.270 --> 00:21:10.640 align:middle line:84%
a slowing down of brain waves
so you see a lot of slow waves

00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:14.300 align:middle line:90%
like theta waves, for instance.

00:21:14.300 --> 00:21:17.000 align:middle line:84%
So when there are
more theta waves,

00:21:17.000 --> 00:21:21.050 align:middle line:84%
it seems that it's associated
with a sort of expansion

00:21:21.050 --> 00:21:24.800 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness and
the sense of self.

00:21:24.800 --> 00:21:26.760 align:middle line:84%
And in that kind
of state, it seems

00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:32.070 align:middle line:84%
easier to be able to work
out psychological problems

00:21:32.070 --> 00:21:35.910 align:middle line:90%
or even physical symptoms.

00:21:35.910 --> 00:21:39.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: You speak, too,
about the consciousness,

00:21:39.810 --> 00:21:41.440 align:middle line:90%
the cosmic consciousness even.

00:21:41.440 --> 00:21:44.300 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if it's how you
say it in English, as well,

00:21:44.300 --> 00:21:47.380 align:middle line:84%
but in your French book--
is that, describe us that--

00:21:47.380 --> 00:21:49.530 align:middle line:90%
what is that term, cosmic--

00:21:49.530 --> 00:21:51.540 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well,
in that state,

00:21:51.540 --> 00:21:57.250 align:middle line:84%
the little self
vanishes totally and you

00:21:57.250 --> 00:22:01.520 align:middle line:84%
become united with everything
that exists in the cosmos

00:22:01.520 --> 00:22:04.700 align:middle line:84%
and even with the
intelligent source

00:22:04.700 --> 00:22:06.500 align:middle line:90%
at the origin of everything.

00:22:06.500 --> 00:22:08.190 align:middle line:84%
And this kind of
experience has been

00:22:08.190 --> 00:22:13.424 align:middle line:84%
reported across history
in various traditions.

00:22:13.424 --> 00:22:14.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: And this
is a place where

00:22:14.840 --> 00:22:16.150 align:middle line:90%
spontaneous healing happens?

00:22:16.150 --> 00:22:17.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what happens
in this state?

00:22:17.770 --> 00:22:21.050 align:middle line:84%
Because often we
speak about unity.

00:22:21.050 --> 00:22:24.620 align:middle line:84%
What does that mean for you
from a scientific perspective?

00:22:24.620 --> 00:22:30.240 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well, it means
that we're not really confined

00:22:30.240 --> 00:22:31.810 align:middle line:90%
to our brains and our bodies.

00:22:31.810 --> 00:22:37.220 align:middle line:84%
We are much more than-- we
are basically interconnected.

00:22:37.220 --> 00:22:40.670 align:middle line:84%
So this is very important
because, in those states,

00:22:40.670 --> 00:22:43.220 align:middle line:84%
you realize that you're
united with everything that

00:22:43.220 --> 00:22:50.490 align:middle line:84%
exists at all sorts of levels,
including what we call matter,

00:22:50.490 --> 00:22:54.800 align:middle line:84%
trees, and so on and so
forth, animals, other humans.

00:22:54.800 --> 00:22:58.540 align:middle line:84%
But also it can be also other
spiritual entities and so on

00:22:58.540 --> 00:23:04.300 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, up to what seems
to be the source of everything

00:23:04.300 --> 00:23:06.210 align:middle line:90%
in the cosmos.

00:23:06.210 --> 00:23:08.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Is this why some
people do meditation?

00:23:08.830 --> 00:23:10.340 align:middle line:84%
I know you're big
on meditations.

00:23:10.340 --> 00:23:12.030 align:middle line:90%
And you've tested.

00:23:12.030 --> 00:23:14.650 align:middle line:84%
Tell us some of the things that
you found in the meditation.

00:23:14.650 --> 00:23:18.187 align:middle line:84%
And do they-- Are people
really-- Do monks try to get

00:23:18.187 --> 00:23:18.770 align:middle line:90%
to this level?

00:23:18.770 --> 00:23:20.702 align:middle line:84%
Is that what we call
enlightenment for some?

00:23:20.702 --> 00:23:21.910 align:middle line:90%
>>BEAUREGARD: Well, yes, yes.

00:23:21.910 --> 00:23:25.100 align:middle line:84%
It's called enlightenment
in certain traditions.

00:23:25.100 --> 00:23:31.870 align:middle line:84%
But to be honest with you,
many people try meditation

00:23:31.870 --> 00:23:35.310 align:middle line:84%
but they will never
get to that point.

00:23:35.310 --> 00:23:37.790 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes, it's
very interesting

00:23:37.790 --> 00:23:41.090 align:middle line:84%
because some people have
these experiences-- they reach

00:23:41.090 --> 00:23:44.950 align:middle line:84%
these states but they never
did anything to get there.

00:23:44.950 --> 00:23:48.640 align:middle line:84%
It seems to happen
spontaneously.

00:23:48.640 --> 00:23:50.670 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe that
there may be other factors

00:23:50.670 --> 00:23:54.480 align:middle line:84%
but we don't know much
about those factors.

00:23:54.480 --> 00:23:58.020 align:middle line:84%
But, no, the studies we've
done about meditation,

00:23:58.020 --> 00:24:02.860 align:middle line:84%
it was more to measure the
impact on the emotional portion

00:24:02.860 --> 00:24:05.770 align:middle line:84%
of the brain, the emotional
brain, that we call.

00:24:05.770 --> 00:24:08.370 align:middle line:84%
It's also called
the limbic system.

00:24:08.370 --> 00:24:13.270 align:middle line:84%
And so what we measured is
that after only a few months

00:24:13.270 --> 00:24:18.310 align:middle line:84%
of practice of what
we call mindfulness--

00:24:18.310 --> 00:24:21.740 align:middle line:84%
it's a key technique in Buddhist
meditation, mindfulness.

00:24:21.740 --> 00:24:24.850 align:middle line:90%


00:24:24.850 --> 00:24:26.800 align:middle line:84%
The regions of
the brain that are

00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:29.710 align:middle line:84%
involved in emotional
responsiveness,

00:24:29.710 --> 00:24:32.660 align:middle line:90%
they quiet down a lot.

00:24:32.660 --> 00:24:36.870 align:middle line:84%
And so the brain is not
as reactive as before.

00:24:36.870 --> 00:24:39.120 align:middle line:84%
So you can produce
such an effect

00:24:39.120 --> 00:24:41.370 align:middle line:84%
after only a few
months of practice.

00:24:41.370 --> 00:24:44.610 align:middle line:84%
Again, it's neural
plasticity, which

00:24:44.610 --> 00:24:45.887 align:middle line:90%
we were talking about earlier.

00:24:45.887 --> 00:24:46.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Yeah, yeah.

00:24:46.720 --> 00:24:49.272 align:middle line:84%
And there's activation of
some portions of the brain.

00:24:49.272 --> 00:24:51.230 align:middle line:84%
I think it's in this book
that you speak of it.

00:24:51.230 --> 00:24:56.540 align:middle line:84%
And you even got to research
on Carmelites or something.

00:24:56.540 --> 00:24:58.720 align:middle line:84%
And they're praying so
it's not just meditation.

00:24:58.720 --> 00:25:00.070 align:middle line:90%
It's a certain openness.

00:25:00.070 --> 00:25:01.200 align:middle line:90%
How would you call that?

00:25:01.200 --> 00:25:05.490 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yes, well, it
was-- with the Carmelite nuns,

00:25:05.490 --> 00:25:07.300 align:middle line:84%
they were talking
more of a state

00:25:07.300 --> 00:25:09.550 align:middle line:90%
of prayer and contemplation.

00:25:09.550 --> 00:25:12.975 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: The
attitude and-- grace.

00:25:12.975 --> 00:25:14.600 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yes,
because they believe

00:25:14.600 --> 00:25:18.780 align:middle line:84%
that, if you have a very
intense mystical experience,

00:25:18.780 --> 00:25:20.620 align:middle line:84%
in their tradition,
they will believe

00:25:20.620 --> 00:25:23.030 align:middle line:84%
that it's because
of God's grace.

00:25:23.030 --> 00:25:26.650 align:middle line:84%
So they don't believe that--
contrary to the Eastern

00:25:26.650 --> 00:25:30.400 align:middle line:84%
traditions-- they don't believe
that you can do or practice

00:25:30.400 --> 00:25:34.150 align:middle line:84%
certain things-- for instance,
prayer and contemplation--

00:25:34.150 --> 00:25:36.690 align:middle line:84%
and that will
dramatically get there.

00:25:36.690 --> 00:25:40.100 align:middle line:84%
Because it depends
on God's will.

00:25:40.100 --> 00:25:43.360 align:middle line:84%
And so, it's a totally
different approach

00:25:43.360 --> 00:25:46.022 align:middle line:90%
than the Eastern traditions.

00:25:46.022 --> 00:25:49.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: But could that explain
how and why some people just

00:25:49.940 --> 00:25:53.010 align:middle line:84%
receive, all of a sudden,
something, some information

00:25:53.010 --> 00:25:56.360 align:middle line:84%
or all of a sudden they
see unity everywhere.

00:25:56.360 --> 00:26:00.220 align:middle line:84%
Or they have those mystical
experience, I mean, how-- Yeah.

00:26:00.220 --> 00:26:02.870 align:middle line:84%
Or being open to that
or having a relationship

00:26:02.870 --> 00:26:04.670 align:middle line:90%
even a god experience.

00:26:04.670 --> 00:26:07.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, being already, what
is the context because there

00:26:07.760 --> 00:26:10.120 align:middle line:84%
must be some fertile
grounds for it.

00:26:10.120 --> 00:26:14.520 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yeah, but we
don't know much about this.

00:26:14.520 --> 00:26:17.700 align:middle line:84%
For sure, in order
to experience this,

00:26:17.700 --> 00:26:20.710 align:middle line:84%
you need a major
change, in terms

00:26:20.710 --> 00:26:22.150 align:middle line:84%
of what's happening
in your brain,

00:26:22.150 --> 00:26:26.220 align:middle line:84%
electrically and chemically,
because, otherwise, it's

00:26:26.220 --> 00:26:27.150 align:middle line:90%
not possible.

00:26:27.150 --> 00:26:32.370 align:middle line:84%
You focus mostly on what's
happening outside your body

00:26:32.370 --> 00:26:33.690 align:middle line:90%
and also inside your body.

00:26:33.690 --> 00:26:37.380 align:middle line:90%
But that's about it.

00:26:37.380 --> 00:26:42.150 align:middle line:84%
You need a shift, in terms
of the brain activity.

00:26:42.150 --> 00:26:48.420 align:middle line:84%
And this shift can bring
you to these type of states.

00:26:48.420 --> 00:26:52.630 align:middle line:84%
But they believe that--
so, we believe now

00:26:52.630 --> 00:26:56.020 align:middle line:84%
that the brain acts as
a filter normally, which

00:26:56.020 --> 00:26:58.140 align:middle line:84%
means that it prevents
you from reaching

00:26:58.140 --> 00:27:01.330 align:middle line:90%
those high spiritual states.

00:27:01.330 --> 00:27:05.960 align:middle line:84%
So we focus mostly on
our biological needs

00:27:05.960 --> 00:27:09.980 align:middle line:84%
and primary psychological
needs and so on and so forth,

00:27:09.980 --> 00:27:13.340 align:middle line:84%
and what we call
the external world.

00:27:13.340 --> 00:27:15.890 align:middle line:84%
But if you do
something that allows

00:27:15.890 --> 00:27:19.710 align:middle line:84%
you to shift your electrical and
chemical activity in the brain,

00:27:19.710 --> 00:27:21.960 align:middle line:84%
even for a few
minutes, for instance,

00:27:21.960 --> 00:27:25.190 align:middle line:84%
if you take
psychedelic substance,

00:27:25.190 --> 00:27:30.830 align:middle line:84%
then you disactivate the
filter function of the brain.

00:27:30.830 --> 00:27:34.400 align:middle line:84%
And then you can have
access to these things,

00:27:34.400 --> 00:27:36.856 align:middle line:90%
these other realms of reality.

00:27:36.856 --> 00:27:38.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: More and
more people are

00:27:38.230 --> 00:27:39.960 align:middle line:90%
very open to speaking of this.

00:27:39.960 --> 00:27:42.910 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it really happens
often in interviews.

00:27:42.910 --> 00:27:45.670 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking of Graham
Hancock and David Icke

00:27:45.670 --> 00:27:48.820 align:middle line:84%
and all these really
state loudly and clearly

00:27:48.820 --> 00:27:52.483 align:middle line:84%
that they have done, and that
they have or Ramdas, of course.

00:27:52.483 --> 00:27:53.441 align:middle line:90%
>>BEAUREGARD: Yes, yes.

00:27:53.441 --> 00:27:57.060 align:middle line:84%
But it can happen also
with sensory deprivation.

00:27:57.060 --> 00:28:01.100 align:middle line:84%
You can be in a sensory
tank, for instance.

00:28:01.100 --> 00:28:05.030 align:middle line:84%
And also, like I was saying,
spontaneously apparently.

00:28:05.030 --> 00:28:11.720 align:middle line:84%
So we know perhaps it comes
from directly, in those cases,

00:28:11.720 --> 00:28:13.290 align:middle line:84%
there was an
intervention directly

00:28:13.290 --> 00:28:16.110 align:middle line:84%
from what people call
the spiritual world.

00:28:16.110 --> 00:28:16.870 align:middle line:90%
Who knows.

00:28:16.870 --> 00:28:19.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Yeah, but the
brain, how does the brain

00:28:19.140 --> 00:28:21.110 align:middle line:84%
evolve through all
those different,

00:28:21.110 --> 00:28:23.150 align:middle line:84%
through the meditation,
through being open,

00:28:23.150 --> 00:28:27.050 align:middle line:84%
through being in the gratitude,
through being spiritual--

00:28:27.050 --> 00:28:29.140 align:middle line:84%
like developing a
spiritual brain.

00:28:29.140 --> 00:28:31.560 align:middle line:84%
How does it, what
does it look like?

00:28:31.560 --> 00:28:33.000 align:middle line:90%
And is it permanent?

00:28:33.000 --> 00:28:37.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you spoke of neural
plasticity but was there some

00:28:37.400 --> 00:28:41.030 align:middle line:84%
kind of studies that show how
our brains are really evolving

00:28:41.030 --> 00:28:44.210 align:middle line:84%
from where they were before to
where they're now to long-term

00:28:44.210 --> 00:28:46.860 align:middle line:90%
and-- mystical side, people--

00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:50.690 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: No, there's
never been such a study.

00:28:50.690 --> 00:28:53.570 align:middle line:84%
They are only have
been brain imaging

00:28:53.570 --> 00:28:57.750 align:middle line:84%
studies of different spiritual
states or meditative states.

00:28:57.750 --> 00:29:01.330 align:middle line:84%
But it's you take a snapshot of
what's happening in the brain

00:29:01.330 --> 00:29:03.080 align:middle line:90%
during a few minutes only.

00:29:03.080 --> 00:29:06.530 align:middle line:84%
But no, this kind of project
has never been done so far.

00:29:06.530 --> 00:29:07.610 align:middle line:90%
So we don't know how--

00:29:07.610 --> 00:29:11.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: But the activity
would move, right?

00:29:11.090 --> 00:29:13.080 align:middle line:84%
>>BEAUREGARD: I
think, well, based

00:29:13.080 --> 00:29:15.390 align:middle line:90%
on what we've done so far, yes.

00:29:15.390 --> 00:29:22.090 align:middle line:84%
The activity in many regions
of the brain seems to change.

00:29:22.090 --> 00:29:26.820 align:middle line:84%
So it would probably change
for a long period of time.

00:29:26.820 --> 00:29:33.270 align:middle line:84%
And it would allow you to
be able to synchronize,

00:29:33.270 --> 00:29:36.360 align:middle line:84%
to catch other
frequencies, if you will.

00:29:36.360 --> 00:29:41.960 align:middle line:84%
So the brain becomes like a
transducer or a transponder

00:29:41.960 --> 00:29:46.720 align:middle line:84%
of other ranges of,
well, frequencies

00:29:46.720 --> 00:29:49.406 align:middle line:84%
or aspects of
reality, if you will.

00:29:49.406 --> 00:29:51.155 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: The creator
of the consciousness.

00:29:51.155 --> 00:29:55.180 align:middle line:90%


00:29:55.180 --> 00:29:59.125 align:middle line:84%
What does the light, the
role of the light itself,

00:29:59.125 --> 00:30:02.140 align:middle line:84%
the light carries
information, doesn't it?

00:30:02.140 --> 00:30:06.240 align:middle line:84%
Is it something that
you looked at, or?

